influencers.name: Gordon Linoff
influencers.description:
Recognized authority on business applications of data mining, including survival data mining.

Founder of Data Miners, Inc. (www.data-miners.com), a consultancy specializing in the analysis of large volumes of data for marketing and CRM purposes. Many clients are in subscription-based industries such as telecommunications, financial services, and newspapers.

I am currently and have been employed by Data Miners since 1998. My work history includes positions where I was or am a part-time consultant, typically because someone else on LinkedIn recognized me as a "colleague".

Author of four books:
"Data Analysis Using SQL and Excel", 2008. Gordon S. Linoff. (http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0471416096/thedataminers)

"Data Mining Techniques for Marketing, Sales, and Customer Relationship Management, Second Edition", 2004. Michael J. A. Berry and Gordon S. Linoff. (http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0471470643/thedataminers)

"Mining the Web: Transforming Customer Data Into Customer Value", 2001. Michael J. A. Berry and Gordon S. Linoff. (http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0471416096/thedataminers)

"Mastering Data Mining: The Art and Science of Customer Relationship Management", 1999. Michael J. A. Berry and Gordon S. Linoff. (http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0471331236/thedataminers)

Author (with Michael Berry) of three well-regarded books in the field: Data Mining Techniques, Mastering Data Mining, and Mining the Web. All are published by John Wiley & Sons.

Specialties: Data mining
Predictive Modeling
Survival Analysis, particularly business applications
Churn and Retention Modeling
Customer-Level Forecasting
Customer Segmentation
Analysis of Large Volumes of Data in SQL Databases
